latestIgtvVideos.title: Virah (Bandish Bandits) • Dance cover
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
'Virah', this beautiful song captures the deep sense of sorrow and pain arising out of separation. The Nayika here is so distressed by the separation (Virahotkanthita) from her beloved that she even hallucinates its presence.

Here, I have tried to portray a blend of Shringara (love) and Karunyam rasa (compassion) two of the Navarasa, or 9 moods, as enumerated in the Natyashastra. 
Karuna is what I find the most difficult one, so definitely had to step out my comfort zone for this piece. For the same reason, I was exceptionally excited and equally nervous at the same time creating this.

I hope I was able to do justice to the song and could deliver you the essence of this composition through my art.
.
